# Scheduled Tasks

This directory contains templates for running sync and reflection on a schedule.

## macOS (launchd)

Two `.plist` files are provided:

| File | Schedule | What it runs |
|------|----------|--------------|
| `com.claude.daily-sync.plist` | Daily at 20:00 | `data-sync` skill |
| `com.claude.weekly-reflect.plist` | Sunday at 09:00 | `weekly-reflection` skill |

### Install

```bash
# Copy plists into LaunchAgents
cp config/com.claude.daily-sync.plist ~/Library/LaunchAgents/
cp config/com.claude.weekly-reflect.plist ~/Library/LaunchAgents/

# Load
launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.claude.daily-sync.plist
launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.claude.weekly-reflect.plist

# Verify
launchctl list | grep com.claude
```

### Logs

- Daily sync: `logs/sync-stdout.log`, `logs/sync-stderr.log`
- Weekly reflect: `logs/reflect-stdout.log`, `logs/reflect-stderr.log`

### Uninstall

```bash
launchctl unload ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.claude.daily-sync.plist
launchctl unload ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.claude.weekly-reflect.plist
rm ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.claude.daily-sync.plist
rm ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.claude.weekly-reflect.plist
```

### Prerequisite: Full Disk Access

On recent macOS, the launchd-spawned process needs Full Disk Access to read email, browser, and other sources. Grant it to:

- `/opt/homebrew/bin/uv` (the binary invoked by the plist)
- Or Terminal.app if you prefer to run manually

System Settings → Privacy & Security → Full Disk Access.

### Customizing the schedule

Edit the `StartCalendarInterval` dict. `Weekday` uses `0 = Sunday`, `1 = Monday`, etc.

```xml
<key>StartCalendarInterval</key>
<dict>
    <key>Hour</key><integer>7</integer>
    <key>Minute</key><integer>30</integer>
</dict>
```

For multiple run times, make `StartCalendarInterval` an array of dicts.

## Linux (cron)

Use `crontab.example` instead. Install with:

```bash
crontab -e
# then paste the lines from config/crontab.example
```

## Manual Runs

Any time:

```bash
uv run .claude/skills/data-sync/sync_all.py --yes
uv run .claude/skills/weekly-reflection/weekly_reflection.py
```
